@Deleted User there is room on the market for more than one solution. don't dismiss the importance of scaling tho...
in 2017 whenever there was a big ERC20 token ICO the whole network crawled to a halt and fees went through the roof. also everybody remembers the CryptoKitties effect
it really is not a good idea to build something with certain expectations for price, throughput, etc and then suddenly discover that to keep using it you have no other option, but pay waaaayy more than you initially anticipated/calculated.
